codexes.text:
&ldquo;Our foes of late have been myriad. Each had decided by instinct or willful intent that humanity&rsquo;s time was over.

&ldquo;We disagreed; none of us more vehemently than you. What you and your allies have done for this system cannot be measured in worth. And I would call on your Light again, to lead Strike missions across every world. Set some records&mdash;serve as inspiration for the new Guardians who join us every day and give them a pinnacle to reach for. The Vanguard is watching.&rdquo;
Commander Zavala

&ldquo;These are the traditions of the City, Guardian. We share them with you so you might better understand those whom you protect.&rdquo;
- Eva Levante


 &ldquo;To live is to experience loss,&rdquo; Eva said. &ldquo;My husband and child are dead. My friends, my neighbors, the children I watched over on our road to the City... all gone now. The festival celebrates their lives with both joy and sorrow.&rdquo;

&ldquo;A fine tradition for the City,&rdquo; Ikora Rey replied. &ldquo;What meaning does it hold for the Guardians?&rdquo;

&ldquo;A bit of Light in a dark time. That is enough.&rdquo;

&ldquo;We have greater concerns. And this is no time for games.&rdquo;

&ldquo;All Guardians were lost once,&rdquo; said Eva. &ldquo;We honor your spirits as well.&rdquo;

&quot;Be brave and fast, Guardian. Racin&#39; is about more than runnin&#39; away.&quot;
- Amanda Holliday


 Some might see racing through the heart of Vex territory as foolhardy. When Shaxx sent his Redjacks to mark up the SRL track on Venus, however, he ordered them to find a location worthy of bravest and most skilled of Guardians.

&ldquo;You&rsquo;d think the fact you took out their High Priest would slow the Splicers down. No such luck.

&ldquo;I&rsquo;m tracking reports of Fallen Splicers spotted in and around the Hellmouth. Intel suggests they&rsquo;re hunting Ogres. Get down there and make sure they don&rsquo;t snatch up any more fodder for their twisted experiments.&quot;
Shiro-4

Icarus


